The ideal candidate should have a strong understanding of DAX formulas and functions, as well as experience working with Power BI.

Skills required:
- Proficiency in Power BI and DAX
- Strong knowledge of data modeling and analysis
- Ability to work with large datasets

item.description:
I am looking for an analyst on a part-time or full-time basis who can work many hours a week depending on availability and skillset (any time zone is fine)

You will be required to log on remotely to complete certain tasks. Time is required or we can switch to a per-milestone contract

MUST HAVE HIGH-SPEED INTERNET CONNECTION and at least 16GB Of RAM on the computer. Microsoft PowerBI installed

MUST BE WILLING TO VALIDATE WORK, it is not enough to write a formula and hope for the best

Looking for an experienced analyst
Examples of tasks:
-Create a report from SQL DB (MySQL, SQL Server, Oracle, Snowflake)
-Finding insights and drawing conclusions
- Statistical analysis using JMP|SAS|
- Advanced knowledge of Python| R
-Creating reports or dashboards in PowerBI or PowerPoint
-Asking questions, and figuring out answers to problems by being proactive



NOT LOOKING FOR A DEVELOPER who JUST FOLLOWS ORDERS looking for someone who can provide solutions and ASK QUESTIONS.


40% of the time is spent analyzing data. It is not enough to create a measure or show a chart must dig into the data. What is the data telling us? these fields are blank is this ok? so many nulls is this right? etc.

40% asking the right questions in order to comprehend and create the business intelligence report. being innovative and condensing disparate pieces of data into actionable insights or succinct reports for senior executives. Proficient with PowerBI, Mcode, and DAX

20 % documentation to help translate business requirements to technical requirements

-Use current and emerging Statistics, Machine Learning and Data Science methods
Innovate new analytic solutions that serve unmet customer needs
communicate analytical results clearly and succinctly-
-Work closely with me to make value-added analytical services available to stakeholders
-Be creative, collaborative in nature, and a self-starter

Must have:
PowerBI
SQL (CTE's, window functions, etc)
Understanding of statistics using R or Python
Some knowledge of statistical viz packages such as JMP, SAS

item.title: Power BI Developer with Microsoft Dynamics 365 Business Central and Power Platform Experience - Upwork
item.description:
Job Title: Power BI Developer with Microsoft Dynamics 365 Business Central and Power Platform Experience

Job Description:
We are seeking a skilled Power BI Developer with extensive experience in Microsoft Dynamics 365 Business Central, NAV, and the Power Platform. The ideal candidate should have a solid background in Power BI, Power Apps (Model Driven App, Power Apps Portals, Canvas App), FetchXML Queries, API Calls in Portals, and Power Automate. Familiarity with Azure Functions, Azure Blob Storage, and Power Apps Portals OOB customizations is essential.

Responsibilities:
- Develop and maintain Power BI reports and dashboards.
- Integrate Power BI with Microsoft Dynamics 365 Business Central and NAV.
- Design and implement Power Apps solutions (Model Driven App, Canvas App).
- Create and manage Power Apps Portals including customizations.
- Utilize FetchXML Queries for data retrieval.
- Implement API calls and integrate with various platforms.
- Develop and automate workflows using Power Automate.
- Utilize Azure Functions and Azure Blob Storage as required.
- Ensure security and permissions management within Microsoft Dynamics 365 and Power Platform.

Requirements:
- 2+ years of experience in Power BI development.
- 2+ years of experience with Microsoft Dynamics 365 BC/NAV
- 2+ years of experience with Microsoft Power Apps Portals.
- 1+ year of experience with Microsoft Power Automate.
- 1+ year of experience with Business Central ERP.

Preferred Skills:
- Working with Business Central/NAV
- Experience on D365 BC Cloud.
- Experience on Business Central Cloud or on-premise version.
- Experience on Al Development & Extension.
- Experience on azure functions development.
- RDLC report development in Visual Studio
- NAV/SQL permissions configuration.
- Third party applications development (ISV).
- .NET development (XmlDOM, REST API, file management).
- Working with web services.
- Development and Testing.
- Developing components And verticals solution.
-Integration Navision With SharePoint.
-FRD and Gap - FIT preparation.
-Project Documentation (Technical) & User Training and TDD Documentation .
- Customer GO live And off line support.
-Hands on experience in AL.

Additional Information:
This is a remote position. Please provide examples of previous work and certifications related to Microsoft Dynamics 365 and Power Platform. The candidate should demonstrate excellent communication skills and the ability to work independently.

If you meet these qualifications and are interested in joining our team, please apply with your updated resume and portfolio. We look forward to hearing from you!

Application Instructions:
To apply, please submit your proposal outlining your relevant experience, portfolio, and availability. Candidates who do not meet the specified qualifications need not apply.

Hourly Range: $20.00-$54.00
Posted On: June 28, 2024 20:47 UTC
Category: Data Visualization
Skills:Data Visualization, API Integration, Dashboard, Digital Mapping, Presentations, Microsoft Power BI, Microsoft Dynamics 365, SQL, Business Intelligence
Skills: Data Visualization, API Integration, Dashboard, Digital Mapping, Presentations, Microsoft Power BI, Microsoft Dynamics 365, SQL, Business Intelligence

item.title: Data Collection and Analysis Specialist - Upwork
item.description:
We’re looking for a detailed and tech-savvy Data Collection and Analysis Specialist to join our team. In this role, you'll dive into our retailers' booking software to gather and analyze data, helping us figure out the lifetime value (LTV) of our clients. If you’re someone who loves data and can pull and analyze it efficiently, we’d love to meet you!

Responsibilities:
- Access and navigate various booking software platforms to pull relevant data.
- Organize and input the collected data into spreadsheets or our preferred software.
- Perform detailed analysis to determine client lifetime value (LTV) and ROI.
- Work closely with our marketing and sales teams to share insights and recommendations.
- Ensure data accuracy and keep comprehensive records.
Identify trends and patterns to help inform our strategic decisions.

Minimum Requirements:
- Proficiency in data collection and analysis tools like Excel, Google Sheets, or similar software.
- Strong attention to detail and accuracy.
- Ability to juggle multiple projects and meet deadlines.
- Great communication skills and a collaborative spirit.

Preferred Experience:
- 3+ years of experience as a Data Analyst or in a similar role.
- Experience in a digital marketing or lead generation agency, especially within the wellness and med spa industry.
- Familiarity with booking software systems used by wellness and med spa businesses.
- Advanced analytical skills and experience with data visualization tools (e.g., Tableau, Power BI).

If you love diving into data and can turn it into valuable insights, we’d love to hear from you!


Hourly Range: $3.00
Posted On: June 28, 2024 22:20 UTC
Category: Data Extraction
Skills:Data Collection, Data Analysis, Google Sheets, Digital Marketing, Lead Generation
Skills: Data Collection, Data Analysis, Google Sheets, Digital Marketing, Lead Generation

item.title: Finish Building A Contract Management Dashboard via React - Upwork
item.description:
I am looking for someone to take over this project - it is 85% done but the developer has gone missing and we are looking to get this wrapped up. Need someone that can easily take over this project and has experience with API's and can easily finish this up.

Here was the original post, but please remember most of it is done. We just need the Microsoft or Pax8 API connected, some history work done and an admin page really.

** ORIGINAL POST BELOW***

Scenario for an admin named Mitch

Mitch Logs in to App (either created on PowerBI or React, whichever makes more sense) (SSO w/ Microsoft a huge bonus but not at all required)
Mitch sees a dashboard of Client contracts expiring in 120 days or less. This would include Company Name, Date of Expiry, and Contract Value/MRR (monthly recurring revenue) expiring.
Mitch clicks on “Contracts” then  "+ New Contract"
Mitch fills in:

Company (If can be synced from SyncroMSP (our Professional Services Automation tool that has a public API), even better, if not then this is manual)
Company Name: Random AG Company
Contract Start Date: April 1st, 2023
Contract Term: 24, 36, 48, 60-month selections (chose 60 months)
Contract End Date: Auto-Generated by Term selection
Monthly Recurring Revenue: $2200.00
Contract Value: $2200.00 x 60 months = Value
Contract Computer Users: 10
Contract Email Only Users: 5
Contract Computers: 15
Contract Servers: 2
Contract Locations: 1

^^This could change too if we start adding our VoIP offering instead. Ability to create fields as I wish.

Save

Somewhere we would need to bind this company with Pax8 (our license reseller) so that it knows which subscriptions belong to which company. This could also be done with direct integration to Microsoft with the clients we are Partners for.

Back on the dashboard, maybe there is another main alert of +- Contract Computer Users and Contract Email Only Users

In Pax8 the licenses linked to the values above are as such:

Contract Computer Users =  “M365 Business Premium”
Contract Email Only Users = “Exchange Online Plan 1”

So if the scenario below happens:

10 - Contract Computer Users =  “M365 Business Premium” - 13
5 - Contract Email Only Users = “Exchange Online Plan 1” – 5

We would want an email to be sent stating that they are above their 2-person “grace” for Contracted Computer Users. (I guess we should add a field in the contract about what the “grace” number is)

This should also just be clearly shown on the dashboard (not emailed out), if it is even 1 above on either of those lines so we can be aware of it.

This was my idea when it was Pax8, the same idea exists if we can talk straight to Microsoft and forget about Pax8. Would also like to be able to include costs for these services and have an updated total of what the profit margin is on each one.


Hourly Range: $7.00-$11.00
Posted On: June 28, 2024 01:00 UTC
Category: Full Stack Development
Skills:React, API
Skills: React, API
Country: Canada

item.title: Data Analyst - Upwork
item.description:
Adly is looking for a full-time, remote Data Analyst contractor to join our operations team, supporting our analytics & data engineering initiatives. As a data analyst on the operations team, you will work as a part of cross-functional business and technical teams alongside other data analysts, business leaders, data/BI engineers and other team members to deliver impactful business intelligence and technical data warehouse solutions. The right candidate has a deep understanding of analytics and excels at extracting insights that drive product enhancements. Your expertise in dissecting subscription-based and product data from diverse sources will play a pivotal role in shaping our operational roadmap and optimizing the effectiveness of our portfolio companies. Beyond your analytical skills, we value your ability to develop reporting solutions from start to finish: including pipeline development and data modeling, dashboarding, and KPI development.

Adly is a technology, data, and performance driven portfolio of SaaS subscription and content companies. Our founders have built, acquired, scaled, and sold several SaaS and content businesses, and have added many of those portfolio companies into Adly.

Under Adly’s current umbrella is are multiple social media growth SaaS businesses, a technology driven dating platform, a B2B WiFi marketing platform, ad-driven content sites, and several more to come. We utilize a combination of paid media (Facebook Ads, Google Ads), organic search / SEO strategy, funnel optimization / CRO, and product design to scale user acquisition and maximize retention across the portfolio.

Key Responsibilities:
- Conduct comprehensive analyses of data to derive actionable insights. Generate reports on operations metrics, product usage, customer behavior, and other performance metrics to enhance decision-making processes.
- Create compelling visualizations and dashboards to effectively communicate insights and trends to stakeholders. Use tools like - Preset and Bigquery to present data in an easily understandable and actionable format.
- Evaluate the performance of existing operations and product features through data analysis. Identify areas for improvement and opportunities for feature enhancements based on user feedback, usage patterns, and market trends.
- Develop ETL/ELT pipelines from raw data sources to final reporting while maintaining a commitment to robust data quality standards.
- Partner with teams to design and execute A/B tests and experiments to evaluate the impact of changes to the product.
- Stay updated on industry trends, best practices, and emerging technologies related to data analysis and product management

Minimum Requirements:
- 2+ years of experience in analytical roles
- Mastery of SQL and a strong understanding of data relationships / relational databases
- Proficiency in Python, R, or another programming language
- Proven skills in A/B testing, experiment set-up, and analysis
- Expertise using data insights to drive business and operational goals
- Excellent communication and collaboration skills.

Preferred Qualifications
- Experience working in a subscriptions-based company
Tableau, Looker, Power BI or another Business Intelligence tool expertise.
- Practical experience developing and maintaining complex ETL pipelines
- Experience with DBT, Cloud Composer, Preset
- Experience working in fast-paced environments

Hourly Range: $10.00-$17.00

item.title: Data Visualization - Upwork
item.description:
I need someone to take a look at a report that my system creates. It's a user task summary report.
The way it works is it time stamps how users drag patients through a workflow. I have a floor plan of our patient working area.
The data correlates to the floor plan.
Users take patients into the room and work them up, take them to other rooms and test them, and then take them to rooms to see the doctor.
I want to run a simulation of the work done in a day and visualize how patients are being moved around the office and which technicians are working them up and how long they are taking.
I could envision a cool 3D video rendition of the office layout too like an auto cad drawing with patients and techs moving around. This or an over view look like an Ariel view of the floor plan with colored dots moving from room to room
